"test-chrome-multitag": "npx playwright test --project=chromium --grep '@datadriven|@regression'"
  
7. For JSON validation install AJV npm install ajv
 responseBody = await response.json();

  // JSON Schema
  const schema = {
    type: "object",
    properties: {
      symbol: { type: "string" },
      price: { type: "number" }
    },
    required: ["symbol", "price"]
  };
  
  const ajv = new Ajv();
  const validate = ajv.compile(schema);
  const valid = validate(responseBody);
  expect(valid).toBe(true);

  ===================Docker =======================
  1 (Precondition)- Docker Desktop should be up and running
  
  2. Create a file called 'dockerfile' and provide the commands
  
    FROM  mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.58.2-noble (Imagename - chaneg the version as per your playwright)
    RUN mkdir /app (create a directory)
    WORKDIR /app (make that as workinfg dir)
    COPY . /app (copy everything where docker file is located into this new directory )
    RUN  npm install --force (ignores conflict and constraits)
    RUN npx playwright install (install playwright)
  
  3. Now from the terminal run  commands 

    Steps one by one to be execute on terminal (it automaticaly recognizes dockerfile)

    -docker build -t docker-testrun1 . ( -t [name of the instance]  . for current working directory)
    -docker images willl show all tghe images
    -docker run -it [name of the omage] it will give you the terminakl in docker
    - run the command npm run 'what ever you created'
    - Ctrl D to exit out of docker and come to your terminal machine 
    Note
    ---------
    repeat the above steps in 3 everytime you make any chages in the project
  
  ****Note : The above execution will not generate report in local ....
   it has to be copied that into local machine . That is why we need docker-compose
  ===================Docker Compose ====================================
  The above will not copy the results
A better way to do is through docker-compose file
File name should be 'docker-compose.yaml'
---------------------------------------

services:
  playwright-testrun:
    image: playwright 
    build:
      context: . (current directory)
      dockerfile: ./dockerfile
    command: npm run test-chrome (commad to run)
    volumes:
      - ./playwright-report/:/app/playwright-report (report to be copied to host machine )
      - ./test-results/:/app/test-results (report to be copied to host machine )
      - ./allure-results/:/app/allure-results (allure report to be copied to host machine )

- docker-compose up --build (because we want to build a new image) (this will do everything)
- npx playwright show-report will give the hrml link on local machine (not on docker)
=====================Allure Report==================

Step 1 npm install -D allure-playwright (- D will ensure package will be saved in devDependencies)
Step 2 Add in config file
["allure-playwright", {
      resultsDir: "allure-results" // Optional: specify output directory
    }]
Step 3 : Run your test using npx playwright test 

Step 4 Generate report and ropen the report (--clean oprion is no more)
- (not required for playwright ) npx allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report
- npx allure open allure-report (it will automatically take data form allure -results folder default folder)
- npx allure serve allure-results (will automatically open the reports)
option 2
- npx allure generate "./allure-results" --clean -o allure-report
- npx allure open allure-report
- npx playwright show-latest will show html report or (playwright-report/index.html)
Step 5 (optional ) npm install -D allure-commandline

******For Report to be visible through Jenkin install allure jenkin plugin
=======================Jenkin Integration==================================
If sourece control is integrated then jenki nfile is needed . otherwise directly copy past the jenkinfile content in the jenken textbox
make sure docker desktpo is running . run the below command
======================================================
- docker run -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home jenkins/jenkins:lts

